    "description": "The strategy is an equity core plus tail hedge overlay that conditionally buys SPY put options when implied volatility, proxied by the VIX, is elevated versus its own recent range. Each trading day (30 minutes after the SPY open), it computes a 150 day VIX rank defined as the current VIX level scaled between the trailing 150 day low and high; when this rank exceeds 0.50, the strategy initiates a protective put position intended to monetize volatility spikes and convex downside protection during stressed equity regimes.\n\nThe portfolio maintains a near fully invested long position in SPY at approximately 90 percent notional. When the volatility trigger is active, it selects a SPY put contract roughly 25 days to expiry (within a plus or minus 8 day window) and about 1 percent out of the money, and sizes the option position at approximately 1 contract per 90 SPY shares held (rounded). Positions are monitored daily; any held option is liquidated when it reaches two days to expiry to avoid accelerated theta decay and expiration effects, and the hedge is re established as needed if high volatility conditions persist.",
